# Firebase Hosting

## Firebaserc Configuration

The `.firebaserc` file should contain your Firebase project ID. Create this file with:

```json
{
  "projects": {
    "default": "your-firebase-project-id"
  }
}
```

Replace `your-firebase-project-id` with your actual Firebase project ID.

## Deployment

To deploy manually:
```bash
npm run build
firebase deploy --only hosting
```

## CI/CD

Firebase deployment is automated via GitHub Actions. See `.github/workflows/firebase-deploy.yml`.

### Required Secrets

Add the following secret to your GitHub repository:
- `FIREBASE_TOKEN`: Generate with `firebase login:ci`

## Project Setup

If you haven't set up a Firebase project yet:

1. Go to https://console.firebase.google.com
2. Create a new project or select existing
3. Enable Hosting in the Firebase console
4. Run `firebase init hosting` locally and select your project
5. Copy the project ID to `.firebaserc`
